An Act amending title 18 Virgin Islands Code, section 232 to provide the process for political
parties to choose their nominees for public offices
PROPOSED BY: Senator Alma Francis Heyliger
1 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the Virgin Islands:
2 SECTION 1. Title 18 Virgin Islands Code, section 232 is amended by striking the
3 section and adding a new section 232 as follows:
4 “§ 232. Primary elections
5 Party primary elections must be held in the Virgin Islands on the first Saturday of August
6 for the purpose of choosing candidates for nomination to public offices to be voted on for the
7 ensuing general election. Primary elections must be conducted by the Virgin Islands Elections
8 System. Political parties may opt out of the primary election and instead nominate candidates
9 for public offices through a process of their choosing. Not later than January 30, political
10 parties shall notify the Supervisor of Elections of the process it will use to nominate candidates

2
1 for public offices. Failure to submit the process by the deadline results in the automatic
2 inclusion of the political party in the primary elections.
3 BILL SUMMARY
4 This bill establishes the process for political parties to choose their nominees for public
5 offices.
